<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-216-404  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 216 404.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 5 1990 v11 n10 p5(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI questions source of funds for RBOCs' major lobbying effort.andO;(MCI Communications Corp., regional Bell operating companies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Thyfault, Mary E.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp asks the FCC to audit the regional Belloperating companies (RBOCs) to determine whether they are usingratepayers' money to lobby Congress for deregulation.andP;  The RBOCshave engaged in a multimillion-dollar advertising campaign aimedat urging consumers to pressure Congress to ease restrictions ontheir entry into new lines of business.andP;  Use of ratepayers' moneyexcludes lobbying expenses from revenue requirements and does notallow the public to determine the actual source of funds,according to MCI.andP;  RBOC officials deny MCI's charges and say theyare accounting for expenses.andP;  A draft bill before the HouseSubcommittee on Telecommunications and Finance is spurring theRBOC lobbying effort; some advertising is aimed directly atcongressional members while other ads urge the general public topress for deregulation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (political activity).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Communications IndustryTelephone CompaniesBell Regional Holding CompaniesGovernment RegulationLobbyingUnited States. Federal Communications Commission.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>